        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "Monadic decomposability is a notion of variable independence ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "which asks whether a given formula in a first - order theory is expressible as a Boolean combination of monadic predicates in the theory . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Recently , Veanes et al . showed the usefulness of monadic decomposability in the context of SMT",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "( i.e. the input formula is quantifier - free ) ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "and found various interesting applications",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "including string analysis . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "However , checking monadic decomposability is undecidable in general . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Decidability for certain theories is known",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "( e.g. Presburger Arithmetic , Tarski 's Real - Closed Field ) ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "but there are very few results",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "regarding their computational complexity . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we study monadic decomposability of integer linear arithmetic in the setting of SMT . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "We show that this decision problem is coNP - complete",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "and ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 16,
            "text": "when monadically decomposable ,",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "a formula admits a decomposition of exponential size in the worst case . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "We provide a new application of our results to string constraint solving with length constraints . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "We then extend our results to variadic decomposability ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 18,
            "text": "where predicates could admit multiple free variables",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 19,
            "text": "( in contrast to monadic decomposability ) . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 18,
            "text": "Finally , we give an application to quantifier elimination in integer linear arithmetic",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "where the variables in a block of quantifiers ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "if independent ,",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "could be eliminated with an exponential",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 24,
            "text": "( instead of the standard doubly exponential )",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 24,
            "text": "blow - up . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        }
    ]
}